That he would never uſe other Argument to convince the Papiſts of their opinion of miracles, but by their owne Doctrine, whereunto moſt of their Miracles are altogether repugnant; as for example; 
                     〈◊〉
                   they have, that the picture of our Lady ſhould ſtir, &c. Their Doctrin is, that their Images are but repreſentative, &c. Now what diſproportion appeareth between their opinion and Doctrine? &c.
